pizza.message

Class MenuRequestMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • pizza.message.PizzaMessage
      • pizza.message.MenuRequestMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MenuRequestMessage
extends PizzaMessage
    This Message type contains no data, but simply requests a message. Human-readable encoding of a MenuRequestMessage is defined as simply:

    1 END
    -- written on a separate line. Note that the first line of this representation contains the message type, as per the PizzaMessage documentation.
    Author:
    drdan
